Are you still using GitHub&rsquo;s Atom text editor? Well, here&rsquo;s the bad news - Atom will soon be &ldquo;retired&rdquo;!
GitHub Officially Announces the &ldquo;Retirement&rdquo; of the Atom Code Editor On June 8, Pacific Time, the official GitHub blog officially posted, &ldquo;Today, we&rsquo;re announcing that we&rsquo;ll be archiving Atom on December 15, 2022, and archiving all projects under the organization.&rdquo;
GitHub, for its part, says it has decided to &ldquo;&hellip;discontinue Atom to further our commitment to bringing fast and reliable software development to the cloud through Microsoft Visual Studio code and GitHub code spaces.
